Reports type assertion or type switch on errors, for example, 'err.(*MyErr)' or 'switch err.(type)', and suggests using 'errors.As' instead. Since Go 1.13, errors can be wrapped using the 'fmt.Errorf' function with the '%w' verb. Therefore, type assertion or type switch on errors fails on wrapped errors. The preferred way for checking for a specific error type is to use the errors.As function from the standard library as this function traverses the chain of the wrapped errors while checking for a specific error type. For more information about 'errors.As', refer to working with Errors in Go 1.13. The quick-fix replaces type assertion and type switch on errors with a call to 'errors.As'. Example 'errFoo, ok := err.(*ErrFoo)


switch err.(type) {
